ef="https://www.engadget.com/twitter-puts-strict-cap-on-how-many-tweets-users-can-read-each-day-182623928.html">不同类型的忽视</a>。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/gfycat-is-shutting-down-on-september-1st-180741599.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/gfycat-is-shutting-down-on-september-1st-180741599.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> a9b316dc-beaf-4735-8b38-7259540e78f5</guid><dc:creator>伊戈尔·博尼法西奇</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Sun, 02 Jul 2023 18:07:41 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688321263</ingested><modified> 2023-07-02T18:07:45+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Igor Bonifacic]]></category><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/495573b0-1902-11ee-addf-ae43af878974" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1200" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/495573b0-1902-11ee-addf-ae43af878974" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Screenshot by Igor Bonifacic / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Screenshot of Gfycat front page.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Gfycat]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Apple's next AirPods Pro could feature a built-in temperature sensor]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p><em>彭博社的马克·</em>古尔曼 (Mark Gurman) 在最新的<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/newsletters/2023-07-02/apple-airpods-plans-hearing-test-body-temperature-cheaper-models-usb-c-ljlfwffu">Power On</a>时事通讯中报道称，苹果正在为其音频产品系列开发新的健康功能。第一个可以让你的 AirPods 进行听力测试。正如<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/7/2/23781756/apples-next-airpods-pro-may-check-your-hearing-health-and-take-your-temperature"><em>The Verge</em>指出的</a>那样，AirPods 已经支持听力图配置文件，iOS 可以使用该配置文件来调整耳塞的输出，以适应听力损失。现在，你可以通过<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL2FwcHMuYXBwbGUuY29tL3VzL2FwcC9taW1pLWhlYXJpbmctdGVzdC9pZDkzMjQ5NjY0NSIsImNvbnRlbnRVdWlkIjoiMWUzOTk2MDUtYzg2Yi00ZjVkLWFjZjYtNDJmNGM2Njc0MjNlIn0&amp;signature=AQAAAYuFaJp_zSbGKbz2T1pnKICpRxbAH0jvC6qIvscb-149&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fapps.apple.com%2Fus%2Fapp%2Fmimi-hearing-test%2Fid932496645">Mimi</a>等第三方应用程序生成这些配置文件，因此，如果苹果要推进自己的测试，这将是该公司<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-10-08-apple-macos-sidecar-newer-macs.html">“Sherlocking”第三方开发人员功能</a>的另一个例子。</p><p>另外，Gurman 写道，在 FDA 去年让美国人更容易 <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2022/08/16/health/fda-hearing-aids.html">购买非处方产品</a>后，苹果正在探索如何将 AirPods Pro 作为助听器进行定位和营销。他报告说，作为该计划的一部分，该公司最近聘请了具有传统助听器工作经验的工程师。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>苹果正在开发的 AirPods 的另一项新功能是让耳机测量体温。内置温度传感器是该公司在<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-watch-series-8-real-world-test-130031046.html">Watch Series 8</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-watch-ultra-review-battery-life-compass-gps-hike-130055477.html">Watch Ultra</a>中推出的功能之一。至于为什么苹果要复制其现有产品中已经存在的一项功能，传感器可以从耳道获得比手腕更准确的温度读数。</p><p>古尔曼警告说，这两项功能“还需要几个月甚至几年的时间才能实现”。他报告称，在不久的将来，苹果计划用 USB-C 充电盒更新 AirPods Pro，并补充说该公司的所有音频产品最终也将不再使用 Lighting。所有这些都是苹果为遵守<a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/iphones-switch-usb-c-comply-eu-charger-law-075020117.html">欧盟新的通用充电标准而</a>必须采取的行动的一部分。古尔曼指出：“尽管发生了 USB-C 转变，但我预计不会很快推出全新的 AirPods Pro 硬件。”他指出苹果<a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/airpods-pro-review-second-generation-130048218.html">去年才刚刚更新了这款耳机</a>。</p><p>在此之前，AirPods 用户至少可以期待苹果表示将<a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apples-ios-17-revamps-core-apps-172548767.html">与 iOS 17 一起</a>推出的新软件功能。其中包括一个新的按钮，可以在通话时将自己静音，以及设备切换的改进。古尔曼推测，苹果还可能将第二代 AirPods 的价格从 129 美元永久降低至 99 美元，以使其在与三星、索尼和亚马逊的低成本产品相比时更具竞争力。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/apples-next-airpods-pro-could-feature-a-built-in-Temperature-sensor-162531033.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/apples-next-airpods-pro-could-feature-a-built-in-temperature-sensor-162531033.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 1e399605-c86b-4f5d-acf6-42f4c667423e</guid><dc:creator>伊戈尔·博尼法西奇</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Sun, 02 Jul 2023 16:25:31 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688373137</ingested><modified> 2023-07-03T08:32:22+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Igor Bonifacic]]></category><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-09/9c0c14e0-39fd-11ed-bff7-79b7ce0a4b0e" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html